  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David Hears of Saul\u2019s Death"
      title: "David Hears of Saul\u2019s Death"
      number: 1
      content: '  After the death of Saul, when David had returned from striking
        down the Amalekites, David remained two days in Ziklag. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And on the third day, behold, a man came from Saul\u2019s camp, with
        his clothes torn and dirt on his head. And when he came to David, he fell
        to the ground and paid homage. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "David said to him, \u201CWhere do you come from?\u201D And he said
        to him, \u201CI have escaped from the camp of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And David said to him, \u201CHow did it go? Tell me.\u201D And he
        answered, \u201CThe people fled from the battle, and also many of the people
        have fallen and are dead, and Saul and his son Jonathan are also dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then David said to the young man who told him, \u201CHow do you know
        that Saul and his son Jonathan are dead?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the young man who told him said, \u201CBy chance I happened to
        be on Mount Gilboa, and there was Saul leaning on his spear, and behold,
        the chariots and the horsemen were close upon him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And when he looked behind him, he saw me, and called to me. And I
        answered, \u2018Here I am.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he said to me, \u2018Who are you?\u2019 I answered him, \u2018I
        am an Amalekite.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And he said to me, \u2018Stand beside me and kill me, for anguish
        has seized me, and yet my life still lingers.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So I stood beside him and killed him, because I was sure that he
        could not live after he had fallen. And I took the crown that was on his
        head and the armlet that was on his arm, and I have brought them here to
        my lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then David took hold of his clothes and tore them, and so did all
        the men who were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they mourned and wept and fasted until evening for Saul and for
        Jonathan his son and for the people of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and
        for the house of Israel, because they had fallen by the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And David said to the young man who told him, \u201CWhere do you
        come from?\u201D And he answered, \u201CI am the son of a sojourner, an Amalekite.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "David said to him, \u201CHow is it you were not afraid to put out
        your hand to destroy the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anointed?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then David called one of the young men and said, \u201CGo, execute
        him.\u201D And he struck him down so that he died. "
      comments: []
    - name: "16: David\u2019s Lament for Saul and Jonathan"
      title: "David\u2019s Lament for Saul and Jonathan"
      number: 16
      content: "And David said to him, \u201CYour blood be on your head, for your
        own mouth has testified against you, saying, \u2018I have killed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        anointed.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And David lamented with this lamentation over Saul and Jonathan his
        son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and he said it[[COMMENT(0)]] should be taught to the people of Judah;
        behold, it is written in the Book of Jashar. He said:  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:18 '
        content: "Septuagint; Hebrew , which may be the name of the lament\u2019s
          tuneOr "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CYour glory, O Israel, is slain on your high places!  How the
        mighty have fallen!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  Tell it not in Gath,  publish it not in the streets of Ashkelon, 
        lest the daughters of the Philistines rejoice,lest the daughters of the uncircumcised
        exult.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  \u201CYou mountains of Gilboa,let there be no dew or rain upon
        you,nor fields of offerings![[COMMENT(0)]]For there the shield of the mighty
        was defiled,the shield of Saul, not anointed with oil.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:21 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CFrom the blood of the slain,from the fat of the mighty,  the
        bow of Jonathan turned not back,and the sword of Saul returned not empty.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CSaul and Jonathan, beloved and lovely!In life and in death
        they were not divided;they were swifter than eagles;they were stronger than
        lions.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CYou daughters of Israel, weep over Saul,who clothed you luxuriously
        in scarlet,  who put ornaments of gold on your apparel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  \u201CHow the mighty have fallenin the midst of the battle!\u201CJonathan
        lies slain on your high places.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I am distressed for you, my brother Jonathan;very pleasant have you
        been to me;  your love to me was extraordinary,surpassing the love of women.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  \u201CHow the mighty have fallen,and the weapons of war perished!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Anointed King of Judah'
      title: David Anointed King of Judah
      number: 1
      content: "  After this David inquired of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CShall
        I go up into any of the cities of Judah?\u201D And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to him, \u201CGo up.\u201D David said, \u201CTo which shall I go up?\u201D
        And he said, \u201CTo Hebron.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So David went up there, and his two wives also, Ahinoam of Jezreel
        and Abigail the widow of Nabal of Carmel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And David brought up his men who were with him, everyone with his
        household, and they lived in the towns of Hebron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the men of Judah came, and there they anointed David king over
        the house of Judah.When they told David, \u201CIt was the men of Jabesh-gilead
        who buried Saul,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "David sent messengers to the men of Jabesh-gilead and said to them,
        \u201CMay you be blessed by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, because you
        showed this loyalty to Saul your lord and buried him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now may the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> show steadfast love and faithfulness
        to you. And I will do good to you because you have done this thing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Ish-bosheth Made King of Israel'
      title: Ish-bosheth Made King of Israel
      number: 7
      content: "Now therefore let your hands be strong, and be valiant, for Saul
        your lord is dead, and the house of Judah has anointed me king over them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But Abner the son of Ner, commander of Saul\u2019s army, took Ish-bosheth
        the son of Saul and brought him over to Mahanaim, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and he made him king over Gilead and the Ashurites and Jezreel and
        Ephraim and Benjamin and all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Ish-bosheth, Saul\u2019s son, was forty years old when he began to
        reign over Israel, and he reigned two years. But the house of Judah followed
        David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Battle of Gibeon'
      title: The Battle of Gibeon
      number: 11
      content: 'And the time that David was king in Hebron over the house of Judah
        was seven years and six months.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Abner the son of Ner, and the servants of Ish-bosheth the son of
        Saul, went out from Mahanaim to Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Joab the son of Zeruiah and the servants of David went out and
        met them at the pool of Gibeon. And they sat down, the one on the one side
        of the pool, and the other on the other side of the pool. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Abner said to Joab, \u201CLet the young men arise and compete
        before us.\u201D And Joab said, \u201CLet them arise.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then they arose and passed over by number, twelve for Benjamin and
        Ish-bosheth the son of Saul, and twelve of the servants of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And each caught his opponent by the head and thrust his sword in
        his opponent\u2019s side, so they fell down together. Therefore that place
        was called Helkath-hazzurim,[[COMMENT(0)]] which is at Gibeon. "
      comments:
      - number: '2:16 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the battle was very fierce that day. And Abner and the men of
        Israel were beaten before the servants of David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the three sons of Zeruiah were there, Joab, Abishai, and Asahel.
        Now Asahel was as swift of foot as a wild gazelle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Asahel pursued Abner, and as he went, he turned neither to the
        right hand nor to the left from following Abner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Abner looked behind him and said, \u201CIs it you, Asahel?\u201D
        And he answered, \u201CIt is I.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Abner said to him, \u201CTurn aside to your right hand or to your
        left, and seize one of the young men and take his spoil.\u201D But Asahel
        would not turn aside from following him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Abner said again to Asahel, \u201CTurn aside from following me.
        Why should I strike you to the ground? How then could I lift up my face to
        your brother Joab?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But he refused to turn aside. Therefore Abner struck him in the stomach
        with the butt of his spear, so that the spear came out at his back. And he
        fell there and died where he was. And all who came to the place where Asahel
        had fallen and died, stood still.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But Joab and Abishai pursued Abner. And as the sun was going down
        they came to the hill of Ammah, which lies before Giah on the way to the
        wilderness of Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And the people of Benjamin gathered themselves together behind Abner
        and became one group and took their stand on the top of a hill. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Abner called to Joab, \u201CShall the sword devour forever?
        Do you not know that the end will be bitter? How long will it be before you
        tell your people to turn from the pursuit of their brothers?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And Joab said, \u201CAs God lives, if you had not spoken, surely
        the men would not have given up the pursuit of their brothers until the morning.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Joab blew the trumpet, and all the men stopped and pursued Israel
        no more, nor did they fight anymore.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And Abner and his men went all that night through the Arabah. They
        crossed the Jordan, and marching the whole morning, they came to Mahanaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Joab returned from the pursuit of Abner. And when he had gathered
        all the people together, there were missing from David\u2019s servants nineteen
        men besides Asahel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But the servants of David had struck down of Benjamin 360 of Abner\u2019s
        men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: And they took up Asahel and buried him in the tomb of his father,
        which was at Bethlehem. And Joab and his men marched all night, and the day
        broke upon them at Hebron.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abner Joins David'
      title: Abner Joins David
      number: 1
      content: '  There was a long war between the house of Saul and the house of
        David. And David grew stronger and stronger, while the house of Saul became
        weaker and weaker.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  And sons were born to David at Hebron: his firstborn was Amnon,
        of Ahinoam of Jezreel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and his second, Chileab, of Abigail the widow of Nabal of Carmel;
        and the third, Absalom the son of Maacah the daughter of Talmai king of Geshur; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and the fourth, Adonijah the son of Haggith; and the fifth, Shephatiah
        the son of Abital; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and the sixth, Ithream, of Eglah, David\u2019s wife. These were born
        to David in Hebron.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'While there was war between the house of Saul and the house of David,
        Abner was making himself strong in the house of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now Saul had a concubine whose name was Rizpah, the daughter of Aiah.
        And Ish-bosheth said to Abner, \u201CWhy have you gone in to my father\u2019s
        concubine?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Abner was very angry over the words of Ish-bosheth and said,
        \u201CAm I a dog\u2019s head of Judah? To this day I keep showing steadfast
        love to the house of Saul your father, to his brothers, and to his friends,
        and have not given you into the hand of David. And yet you charge me today
        with a fault concerning a woman. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'God do so to Abner and more also, if I do not accomplish for David
        what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sworn to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "to transfer the kingdom from the house of Saul and set up the throne
        of David over Israel and over Judah, from Dan to Beersheba.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Ish-bosheth could not answer Abner another word, because he feared
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Abner sent messengers to David on his behalf,[[COMMENT(0)]] saying,
        \u201CTo whom does the land belong? Make your covenant with me, and behold,
        my hand shall be with you to bring over all Israel to you.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '3:12 '
        content: 'Or ; Septuagint '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he said, \u201CGood; I will make a covenant with you. But one
        thing I require of you; that is, you shall not see my face unless you first
        bring Michal, Saul\u2019s daughter, when you come to see my face.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then David sent messengers to Ish-bosheth, Saul\u2019s son, saying,
        \u201CGive me my wife Michal, for whom I paid the bridal price of a hundred
        foreskins of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Ish-bosheth sent and took her from her husband Paltiel the son
        of Laish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But her husband went with her, weeping after her all the way to Bahurim.
        Then Abner said to him, \u201CGo, return.\u201D And he returned.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Abner conferred with the elders of Israel, saying, \u201CFor
        some time past you have been seeking David as king over you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now then bring it about, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        promised David, saying, \u2018By the hand of my servant David I will save
        my people Israel from the hand of the Philistines, and from the hand of all
        their enemies.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Abner also spoke to Benjamin. And then Abner went to tell David at
        Hebron all that Israel and the whole house of Benjamin thought good to do.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When Abner came with twenty men to David at Hebron, David made a
        feast for Abner and the men who were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Abner said to David, \u201CI will arise and go and will gather
        all Israel to my lord the king, that they may make a covenant with you, and
        that you may reign over all that your heart desires.\u201D So David sent
        Abner away, and he went in peace.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Just then the servants of David arrived with Joab from a raid, bringing
        much spoil with them. But Abner was not with David at Hebron, for he had
        sent him away, and he had gone in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "When Joab and all the army that was with him came, it was told Joab,
        \u201CAbner the son of Ner came to the king, and he has let him go, and he
        has gone in peace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Joab went to the king and said, \u201CWhat have you done? Behold,
        Abner came to you. Why is it that you have sent him away, so that he is gone? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Joab Murders Abner'
      title: Joab Murders Abner
      number: 25
      content: "You know that Abner the son of Ner came to deceive you and to know
        your going out and your coming in, and to know all that you are doing.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When Joab came out from David\u2019s presence, he sent messengers
        after Abner, and they brought him back from the cistern of Sirah. But David
        did not know about it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And when Abner returned to Hebron, Joab took him aside into the midst
        of the gate to speak with him privately, and there he struck him in the stomach,
        so that he died, for the blood of Asahel his brother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Afterward, when David heard of it, he said, \u201CI and my kingdom
        are forever guiltless before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for the blood
        of Abner the son of Ner. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "May it fall upon the head of Joab and upon all his father\u2019s
        house, and may the house of Joab never be without one who has a discharge
        or who is leprous or who holds a spindle or who falls by the sword or who
        lacks bread!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: David Mourns Abner'
      title: David Mourns Abner
      number: 30
      content: 'So Joab and Abishai his brother killed Abner, because he had put
        their brother Asahel to death in the battle at Gibeon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then David said to Joab and to all the people who were with him,
        \u201CTear your clothes and put on sackcloth and mourn before Abner.\u201D
        And King David followed the bier. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'They buried Abner at Hebron. And the king lifted up his voice and
        wept at the grave of Abner, and all the people wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And the king lamented for Abner, saying,  \u201CShould Abner die
        as a fool dies?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Your hands were not bound;your feet were not fettered;as one falls
        before the wickedyou have fallen.\u201DAnd all the people wept again over
        him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then all the people came to persuade David to eat bread while it
        was yet day. But David swore, saying, \u201CGod do so to me and more also,
        if I taste bread or anything else till the sun goes down!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And all the people took notice of it, and it pleased them, as everything
        that the king did pleased all the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "So all the people and all Israel understood that day that it had
        not been the king\u2019s will to put to death Abner the son of Ner. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And the king said to his servants, \u201CDo you not know that a prince
        and a great man has fallen this day in Israel? "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "And I was gentle today, though anointed king. These men, the sons
        of Zeruiah, are more severe than I. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> repay
        the evildoer according to his wickedness!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ish-bosheth Murdered'
      title: Ish-bosheth Murdered
      number: 1
      content: "  When Ish-bosheth, Saul\u2019s son, heard that Abner had died at
        Hebron, his courage failed, and all Israel was dismayed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now Saul\u2019s son had two men who were captains of raiding bands;
        the name of the one was Baanah, and the name of the other Rechab, sons of
        Rimmon a man of Benjamin from Beeroth (for Beeroth also is counted part of
        Benjamin; "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'the Beerothites fled to Gittaim and have been sojourners there to
        this day).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Jonathan, the son of Saul, had a son who was crippled in his feet.
        He was five years old when the news about Saul and Jonathan came from Jezreel,
        and his nurse took him up and fled, and as she fled in her haste, he fell
        and became lame. And his name was Mephibosheth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now the sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, Rechab and Baanah, set out,
        and about the heat of the day they came to the house of Ish-bosheth as he
        was taking his noonday rest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And they came into the midst of the house as if to get wheat, and
        they stabbed him in the stomach. Then Rechab and Baanah his brother escaped.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:6 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When they came into the house, as he lay on his bed in his bedroom,
        they struck him and put him to death and beheaded him. They took his head
        and went by the way of the Arabah all night, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and brought the head of Ish-bosheth to David at Hebron. And they
        said to the king, \u201CHere is the head of Ish-bosheth, the son of Saul,
        your enemy, who sought your life. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has avenged
        my lord the king this day on Saul and on his offspring.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But David answered Rechab and Baanah his brother, the sons of Rimmon
        the Beerothite, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, who has redeemed
        my life out of every adversity, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "when one told me, \u2018Behold, Saul is dead,\u2019 and thought he
        was bringing good news, I seized him and killed him at Ziklag, which was
        the reward I gave him for his news. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "How much more, when wicked men have killed a righteous man in his
        own house on his bed, shall I not now require his blood at your hand and
        destroy you from the earth?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And David commanded his young men, and they killed them and cut off
        their hands and feet and hanged them beside the pool at Hebron. But they
        took the head of Ish-bosheth and buried it in the tomb of Abner at Hebron.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Anointed King of Israel'
      title: David Anointed King of Israel
      number: 1
      content: "  Then all the tribes of Israel came to David at Hebron and said,
        \u201CBehold, we are your bone and flesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "In times past, when Saul was king over us, it was you who led out
        and brought in Israel. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to you, \u2018You
        shall be shepherd of my people Israel, and you shall be prince[[COMMENT(0)]]
        over Israel.\u2019\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '5:2 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So all the elders of Israel came to the king at Hebron, and King
        David made a covenant with them at Hebron before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and they anointed David king over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'David was thirty years old when he began to reign, and he reigned
        forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'At Hebron he reigned over Judah seven years and six months, and at
        Jerusalem he reigned over all Israel and Judah thirty-three years.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:5 '
        content: "Dead Sea Scroll lacks verses 4\u20135"
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  And the king and his men went to Jerusalem against the Jebusites,
        the inhabitants of the land, who said to David, \u201CYou will not come in
        here, but the blind and the lame will ward you off\u201D\u2014thinking, \u201CDavid
        cannot come in here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Nevertheless, David took the stronghold of Zion, that is, the city
        of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And David said on that day, \u201CWhoever would strike the Jebusites,
        let him get up the water shaft to attack \u2018the lame and the blind,\u2019
        who are hated by David\u2019s soul.\u201D Therefore it is said, \u201CThe
        blind and the lame shall not come into the house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And David lived in the stronghold and called it the city of David.
        And David built the city all around from the Millo inward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And David became greater and greater, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of hosts, was with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  And Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David, and cedar trees,
        also carpenters and masons who built David a house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And David knew that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had established
        him king over Israel, and that he had exalted his kingdom for the sake of
        his people Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And David took more concubines and wives from Jerusalem, after he
        came from Hebron, and more sons and daughters were born to David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And these are the names of those who were born to him in Jerusalem:
        Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Solomon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Ibhar, Elishua, Nepheg, Japhia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: David Defeats the Philistines'
      title: David Defeats the Philistines
      number: 16
      content: 'Elishama, Eliada, and Eliphelet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When the Philistines heard that David had been anointed king over
        Israel, all the Philistines went up to search for David. But David heard
        of it and went down to the stronghold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the Philistines had come and spread out in the Valley of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And David inquired of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CShall
        I go up against the Philistines? Will you give them into my hand?\u201D And
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to David, \u201CGo up, for I will certainly
        give the Philistines into your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And David came to Baal-perazim, and David defeated them there. And
        he said, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has broken through my enemies
        before me like a breaking flood.\u201D Therefore the name of that place is
        called Baal-perazim.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:20 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the Philistines left their idols there, and David and his men
        carried them away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the Philistines came up yet again and spread out in the Valley
        of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And when David inquired of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, he said,
        \u201CYou shall not go up; go around to their rear, and come against them
        opposite the balsam trees. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And when you hear the sound of marching in the tops of the balsam
        trees, then rouse yourself, for then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        gone out before you to strike down the army of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And David did as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded him, and
        struck down the Philistines from Geba to Gezer.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ark Brought to Jerusalem'
      title: The Ark Brought to Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '    David again gathered all the chosen men of Israel, thirty thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And David arose and went with all the people who were with him from
        Baale-judah to bring up from there the ark of God, which is called by the
        name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts who sits enthroned on the
        cherubim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And they carried the ark of God on a new cart and brought it out
        of the house of Abinadab, which was on the hill. And Uzzah and Ahio,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the sons of Abinadab, were driving the new cart, '
      comments:
      - number: '6:3 '
        content: Or ; also verse 4
    - name: '4: Uzzah and the Ark'
      title: Uzzah and the Ark
      number: 4
      content: 'with the ark of God,[[COMMENT(0)]] and Ahio went before the ark.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:4 '
        content: 'Compare Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And David and all the house of Israel were celebrating before the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, with songs[[COMMENT(0)]] and lyres and harps
        and tambourines and castanets and cymbals. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:5 '
        content: 'Septuagint, 1 Chronicles 13:8; Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when they came to the threshing floor of Nacon, Uzzah put out
        his hand to the ark of God and took hold of it, for the oxen stumbled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was kindled against
        Uzzah, and God struck him down there because of his error, and he died there
        beside the ark of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And David was angry because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had broken
        out against Uzzah. And that place is called Perez-uzzah[[COMMENT(0)]] to
        this day. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:8 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And David was afraid of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that day,
        and he said, \u201CHow can the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> come
        to me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So David was not willing to take the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        into the city of David. But David took it aside to the house of Obed-edom
        the Gittite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> remained in the house
        of Obed-edom the Gittite three months, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        blessed Obed-edom and all his household.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And it was told King David, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has blessed the household of Obed-edom and all that belongs to him, because
        of the ark of God.\u201D So David went and brought up the ark of God from
        the house of Obed-edom to the city of David with rejoicing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And when those who bore the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had gone six steps, he sacrificed an ox and a fattened animal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And David danced before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with all
        his might. And David was wearing a linen ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: David and Michal'
      title: David and Michal
      number: 15
      content: 'So David and all the house of Israel brought up the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        with shouting and with the sound of the horn.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'As the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came into the city
        of David, Michal the daughter of Saul looked out of the window and saw King
        David leaping and dancing before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and she
        despised him in her heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And they brought in the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and
        set it in its place, inside the tent that David had pitched for it. And David
        offered burnt offerings and peace offerings before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And when David had finished offering the burnt offerings and the
        peace offerings, he blessed the people in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and distributed among all the people, the whole multitude of Israel,
        both men and women, a cake of bread, a portion of meat,[[COMMENT(0)]] and
        a cake of raisins to each one. Then all the people departed, each to his
        house.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:19 '
        content: Vulgate; the meaning of the Hebrew term is uncertain
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And David returned to bless his household. But Michal the daughter
        of Saul came out to meet David and said, \u201CHow the king of Israel honored
        himself today, uncovering himself today before the eyes of his servants\u2019
        female servants, as one of the vulgar fellows shamelessly uncovers himself!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And David said to Michal, \u201CIt was before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        who chose me above your father and above all his house, to appoint me as
        prince[[COMMENT(0)]] over Israel, the people of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014and
        I will celebrate before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments:
      - number: '6:21 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "I will make myself yet more contemptible than this, and I will be
        abased in your[[COMMENT(0)]] eyes. But by the female servants of whom you
        have spoken, by them I shall be held in honor.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '6:22 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And Michal the daughter of Saul had no child to the day of her death.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The \u2019s Covenant with David"
      title: "The \u2019s Covenant with David"
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    Now when the king lived in his house
        and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  had given him rest from all his surrounding
        enemies, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "the king said to Nathan the prophet, \u201CSee now, I dwell in a
        house of cedar, but the ark of God dwells in a tent.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Nathan said to the king, \u201CGo, do all that is in your heart,
        for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is with you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But that same night the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came
        to Nathan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CGo and tell my servant David, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:
        Would you build me a house to dwell in? "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I have not lived in a house since the day I brought up the people
        of Israel from Egypt to this day, but I have been moving about in a tent
        for my dwelling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "In all places where I have moved with all the people of Israel, did
        I speak a word with any of the judges[[COMMENT(0)]] of Israel, whom I commanded
        to shepherd my people Israel, saying, \u201CWhy have you not built me a house
        of cedar?\u201D\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '7:7 '
        content: 'Compare 1 Chronicles 17:6; Hebrew '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now, therefore, thus you shall say to my servant David, \u2018Thus
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, I took you from the pasture,
        from following the sheep, that you should be prince[[COMMENT(0)]] over my
        people Israel. "
      comments:
      - number: '7:8 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And I have been with you wherever you went and have cut off all your
        enemies from before you. And I will make for you a great name, like the name
        of the great ones of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And I will appoint a place for my people Israel and will plant them,
        so that they may dwell in their own place and be disturbed no more. And violent
        men shall afflict them no more, as formerly, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'from the time that I appointed judges over my people Israel. And
        I will give you rest from all your enemies. Moreover, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        declares to you that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will make you a house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When your days are fulfilled and you lie down with your fathers,
        I will raise up your offspring after you, who shall come from your body,
        and I will establish his kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He shall build a house for my name, and I will establish the throne
        of his kingdom forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will be to him a father, and he shall be to me a son. When he commits
        iniquity, I will discipline him with the rod of men, with the stripes of
        the sons of men, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'but my steadfast love will not depart from him, as I took it from
        Saul, whom I put away from before you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And your house and your kingdom shall be made sure forever before
        me.[[COMMENT(0)]]  Your throne shall be established forever.\u2019\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '7:16 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: "17: David\u2019s Prayer of Gratitude"
      title: "David\u2019s Prayer of Gratitude"
      number: 17
      content: 'In accordance with all these words, and in accordance with all this
        vision, Nathan spoke to David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then King David went in and sat before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and said, \u201CWho am I, O Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>, and what is
        my house, that you have brought me thus far? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And yet this was a small thing in your eyes, O Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>.
        You have spoken also of your servant\u2019s house for a great while to come,
        and this is instruction for mankind, O Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>! "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And what more can David say to you? For you know your servant, O
        Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>! '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Because of your promise, and according to your own heart, you have
        brought about all this greatness, to make your servant know it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Therefore you are great, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God. For there
        is none like you, and there is no God besides you, according to all that
        we have heard with our ears. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And who is like your people Israel, the one nation on earth whom
        God went to redeem to be his people, making himself a name and doing for
        them[[COMMENT(0)]] great and awesome things by driving out before your people,
        whom you redeemed for yourself from Egypt, a nation and its gods? '
      comments:
      - number: '7:23 '
        content: 'With a few Targums, Vulgate, Syriac; Hebrew Septuagint (compare
          1 Chronicles 17:21); Hebrew '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And you established for yourself your people Israel to be your people
        forever. And you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, became their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And now, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God, confirm forever the word
        that you have spoken concerning your servant and concerning his house, and
        do as you have spoken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And your name will be magnified forever, saying, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts is God over Israel,\u2019 and the house of your servant David will
        be established before you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "For you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of Israel,
        have made this revelation to your servant, saying, \u2018I will build you
        a house.\u2019 Therefore your servant has found courage to pray this prayer
        to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And now, O Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>, you are God, and your
        words are true, and you have promised this good thing to your servant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Now therefore may it please you to bless the house of your servant,
        so that it may continue forever before you. For you, O Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>,
        have spoken, and with your blessing shall the house of your servant be blessed
        forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Victories"
      title: "David\u2019s Victories"
      number: 1
      content: '    After this David defeated the Philistines and subdued them, and
        David took Metheg-ammah out of the hand of the Philistines.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  And he defeated Moab and he measured them with a line, making them
        lie down on the ground. Two lines he measured to be put to death, and one
        full line to be spared. And the Moabites became servants to David and brought
        tribute.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'David also defeated Hadadezer the son of Rehob, king of Zobah, as
        he went to restore his power at the river Euphrates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And David took from him 1,700 horsemen, and 20,000 foot soldiers.
        And David hamstrung all the chariot horses but left enough for 100 chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And when the Syrians of Damascus came to help Hadadezer king of Zobah,
        David struck down 22,000 men of the Syrians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then David put garrisons in Aram of Damascus, and the Syrians became
        servants to David and brought tribute. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave victory to David wherever he went. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And David took the shields of gold that were carried by the servants
        of Hadadezer and brought them to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And from Betah and from Berothai, cities of Hadadezer, King David
        took very much bronze.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When Toi king of Hamath heard that David had defeated the whole army
        of Hadadezer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Toi sent his son Joram to King David, to ask about his health and
        to bless him because he had fought against Hadadezer and defeated him, for
        Hadadezer had often been at war with Toi. And Joram brought with him articles
        of silver, of gold, and of bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'These also King David dedicated to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        together with the silver and gold that he dedicated from all the nations
        he subdued, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'from Edom, Moab, the Ammonites, the Philistines, Amalek, and from
        the spoil of Hadadezer the son of Rehob, king of Zobah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And David made a name for himself when he returned from striking
        down 18,000 Edomites in the Valley of Salt. '
      comments: []
    - name: "14: David\u2019s Officials"
      title: "David\u2019s Officials"
      number: 14
      content: "Then he put garrisons in Edom; throughout all Edom he put garrisons,
        and all the Edomites became David\u2019s servants. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave victory to David wherever he went.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So David reigned over all Israel. And David administered justice
        and equity to all his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Joab the son of Zeruiah was over the army, and Jehoshaphat the son
        of Ahilud was recorder, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and Zadok the son of Ahitub and Ahimelech the son of Abiathar were
        priests, and Seraiah was secretary, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over[[COMMENT(0)]] the Cherethites
        and the Pelethites, and David\u2019s sons were priests."
      comments:
      - number: '8:18 '
        content: 'Compare 20:23, 1 Chronicles 18:17, Syriac, Targum, Vulgate; Hebrew
          lacks '
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Kindness to Mephibosheth"
      title: "David\u2019s Kindness to Mephibosheth"
      number: 1
      content: "  And David said, \u201CIs there still anyone left of the house of
        Saul, that I may show him kindness for Jonathan\u2019s sake?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now there was a servant of the house of Saul whose name was Ziba,
        and they called him to David. And the king said to him, \u201CAre you Ziba?\u201D
        And he said, \u201CI am your servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the king said, \u201CIs there not still someone of the house
        of Saul, that I may show the kindness of God to him?\u201D Ziba said to the
        king, \u201CThere is still a son of Jonathan; he is crippled in his feet.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The king said to him, \u201CWhere is he?\u201D And Ziba said to the
        king, \u201CHe is in the house of Machir the son of Ammiel, at Lo-debar.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then King David sent and brought him from the house of Machir the
        son of Ammiel, at Lo-debar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Mephibosheth the son of Jonathan, son of Saul, came to David
        and fell on his face and paid homage. And David said, \u201CMephibosheth!\u201D
        And he answered, \u201CBehold, I am your servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And David said to him, \u201CDo not fear, for I will show you kindness
        for the sake of your father Jonathan, and I will restore to you all the land
        of Saul your father, and you shall eat at my table always.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he paid homage and said, \u201CWhat is your servant, that you
        should show regard for a dead dog such as I?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the king called Ziba, Saul\u2019s servant, and said to him,
        \u201CAll that belonged to Saul and to all his house I have given to your
        master\u2019s grandson. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And you and your sons and your servants shall till the land for him
        and shall bring in the produce, that your master\u2019s grandson may have
        bread to eat. But Mephibosheth your master\u2019s grandson shall always eat
        at my table.\u201D Now Ziba had fifteen sons and twenty servants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Ziba said to the king, \u201CAccording to all that my lord the
        king commands his servant, so will your servant do.\u201D So Mephibosheth
        ate at David\u2019s[[COMMENT(0)]] table, like one of the king\u2019s sons. "
      comments:
      - number: '9:11 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Mephibosheth had a young son, whose name was Mica. And all who
        lived in Ziba\u2019s house became Mephibosheth\u2019s servants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So Mephibosheth lived in Jerusalem, for he ate always at the king\u2019s
        table. Now he was lame in both his feet."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Defeats Ammon and Syria'
      title: David Defeats Ammon and Syria
      number: 1
      content: '    After this the king of the Ammonites died, and Hanun his son
        reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And David said, \u201CI will deal loyally[[COMMENT(0)]] with Hanun
        the son of Nahash, as his father dealt loyally with me.\u201D So David sent
        by his servants to console him concerning his father. And David\u2019s servants
        came into the land of the Ammonites. "
      comments:
      - number: '10:2 '
        content: Or ; twice in this verse
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But the princes of the Ammonites said to Hanun their lord, \u201CDo
        you think, because David has sent comforters to you, that he is honoring
        your father? Has not David sent his servants to you to search the city and
        to spy it out and to overthrow it?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Hanun took David\u2019s servants and shaved off half the beard
        of each and cut off their garments in the middle, at their hips, and sent
        them away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When it was told David, he sent to meet them, for the men were greatly
        ashamed. And the king said, \u201CRemain at Jericho until your beards have
        grown and then return.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When the Ammonites saw that they had become a stench to David, the
        Ammonites sent and hired the Syrians of Beth-rehob, and the Syrians of Zobah,
        20,000 foot soldiers, and the king of Maacah with 1,000 men, and the men
        of Tob, 12,000 men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when David heard of it, he sent Joab and all the host of the
        mighty men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the Ammonites came out and drew up in battle array at the entrance
        of the gate, and the Syrians of Zobah and of Rehob and the men of Tob and
        Maacah were by themselves in the open country.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When Joab saw that the battle was set against him both in front and
        in the rear, he chose some of the best men of Israel and arrayed them against
        the Syrians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The rest of his men he put in the charge of Abishai his brother,
        and he arrayed them against the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And he said, \u201CIf the Syrians are too strong for me, then you
        shall help me, but if the Ammonites are too strong for you, then I will come
        and help you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Be of good courage, and let us be courageous for our people, and
        for the cities of our God, and may the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> do what
        seems good to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Joab and the people who were with him drew near to battle against
        the Syrians, and they fled before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And when the Ammonites saw that the Syrians fled, they likewise fled
        before Abishai and entered the city. Then Joab returned from fighting against
        the Ammonites and came to Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But when the Syrians saw that they had been defeated by Israel, they
        gathered themselves together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Hadadezer sent and brought out the Syrians who were beyond the
        Euphrates.[[COMMENT(0)]] They came to Helam, with Shobach the commander of
        the army of Hadadezer at their head. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:16 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And when it was told David, he gathered all Israel together and crossed
        the Jordan and came to Helam. The Syrians arrayed themselves against David
        and fought with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the Syrians fled before Israel, and David killed of the Syrians
        the men of 700 chariots, and 40,000 horsemen, and wounded Shobach the commander
        of their army, so that he died there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: And when all the kings who were servants of Hadadezer saw that they
        had been defeated by Israel, they made peace with Israel and became subject
        to them. So the Syrians were afraid to save the Ammonites anymore.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David and Bathsheba'
      title: David and Bathsheba
      number: 1
      content: '      In the spring of the year, the time when kings go out to battle,
        David sent Joab, and his servants with him, and all Israel. And they ravaged
        the Ammonites and besieged Rabbah. But David remained at Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "It happened, late one afternoon, when David arose from his couch
        and was walking on the roof of the king\u2019s house, that he saw from the
        roof a woman bathing; and the woman was very beautiful. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And David sent and inquired about the woman. And one said, \u201CIs
        not this Bathsheba, the daughter of Eliam, the wife of Uriah the Hittite?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So David sent messengers and took her, and she came to him, and he
        lay with her. (Now she had been purifying herself from her uncleanness.)
        Then she returned to her house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the woman conceived, and she sent and told David, \u201CI am
        pregnant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So David sent word to Joab, \u201CSend me Uriah the Hittite.\u201D
        And Joab sent Uriah to David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When Uriah came to him, David asked how Joab was doing and how the
        people were doing and how the war was going. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then David said to Uriah, \u201CGo down to your house and wash your
        feet.\u201D And Uriah went out of the king\u2019s house, and there followed
        him a present from the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But Uriah slept at the door of the king\u2019s house with all the
        servants of his lord, and did not go down to his house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When they told David, \u201CUriah did not go down to his house,\u201D
        David said to Uriah, \u201CHave you not come from a journey? Why did you
        not go down to your house?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Uriah said to David, \u201CThe ark and Israel and Judah dwell in
        booths, and my lord Joab and the servants of my lord are camping in the open
        field. Shall I then go to my house, to eat and to drink and to lie with my
        wife? As you live, and as your soul lives, I will not do this thing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then David said to Uriah, \u201CRemain here today also, and tomorrow
        I will send you back.\u201D So Uriah remained in Jerusalem that day and the
        next. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And David invited him, and he ate in his presence and drank, so that
        he made him drunk. And in the evening he went out to lie on his couch with
        the servants of his lord, but he did not go down to his house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'In the morning David wrote a letter to Joab and sent it by the hand
        of Uriah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "In the letter he wrote, \u201CSet Uriah in the forefront of the hardest
        fighting, and then draw back from him, that he may be struck down, and die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And as Joab was besieging the city, he assigned Uriah to the place
        where he knew there were valiant men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the men of the city came out and fought with Joab, and some of
        the servants of David among the people fell. Uriah the Hittite also died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Joab sent and told David all the news about the fighting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he instructed the messenger, \u201CWhen you have finished telling
        all the news about the fighting to the king, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "then, if the king\u2019s anger rises, and if he says to you, \u2018Why
        did you go so near the city to fight? Did you not know that they would shoot
        from the wall? "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Who killed Abimelech the son of Jerubbesheth? Did not a woman cast
        an upper millstone on him from the wall, so that he died at Thebez? Why did
        you go so near the wall?\u2019 then you shall say, \u2018Your servant Uriah
        the Hittite is dead also.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So the messenger went and came and told David all that Joab had sent
        him to tell. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The messenger said to David, \u201CThe men gained an advantage over
        us and came out against us in the field, but we drove them back to the entrance
        of the gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then the archers shot at your servants from the wall. Some of the
        king\u2019s servants are dead, and your servant Uriah the Hittite is dead
        also.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "David said to the messenger, \u201CThus shall you say to Joab, \u2018Do
        not let this matter displease you, for the sword devours now one and now
        another. Strengthen your attack against the city and overthrow it.\u2019
        And encourage him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'When the wife of Uriah heard that Uriah her husband was dead, she
        lamented over her husband. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: And when the mourning was over, David sent and brought her to his
        house, and she became his wife and bore him a son. But the thing that David
        had done displeased the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Nathan Rebukes David'
      title: Nathan Rebukes David
      number: 1
      content: "  And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent Nathan to David. He came
        to him and said to him, \u201CThere were two men in a certain city, the one
        rich and the other poor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The rich man had very many flocks and herds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'but the poor man had nothing but one little ewe lamb, which he had
        bought. And he brought it up, and it grew up with him and with his children.
        It used to eat of his morsel and drink from his cup and lie in his arms,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and it was like a daughter to him. '
      comments:
      - number: '12:3 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verse 8
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now there came a traveler to the rich man, and he was unwilling to
        take one of his own flock or herd to prepare for the guest who had come to
        him, but he took the poor man\u2019s lamb and prepared it for the man who
        had come to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then David\u2019s anger was greatly kindled against the man, and
        he said to Nathan, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, the man
        who has done this deserves to die, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and he shall restore the lamb fourfold, because he did this thing,
        and because he had no pity.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Nathan said to David, \u201CYou are the man! Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, \u2018I anointed you king over Israel, and I delivered
        you out of the hand of Saul. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And I gave you your master\u2019s house and your master\u2019s wives
        into your arms and gave you the house of Israel and of Judah. And if this
        were too little, I would add to you as much more. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Why have you despised the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        to do what is evil in his sight? You have struck down Uriah the Hittite with
        the sword and have taken his wife to be your wife and have killed him with
        the sword of the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now therefore the sword shall never depart from your house, because
        you have despised me and have taken the wife of Uriah the Hittite to be your
        wife.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u2018Behold, I will raise
        up evil against you out of your own house. And I will take your wives before
        your eyes and give them to your neighbor, and he shall lie with your wives
        in the sight of this sun. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For you did it secretly, but I will do this thing before all Israel
        and before the sun.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "David said to Nathan, \u201CI have sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D
        And Nathan said to David, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> also has
        put away your sin; you shall not die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Nevertheless, because by this deed you have utterly scorned the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the child who is born to you shall die.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '12:14 '
        content: 'Masoretic Text <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>;
          Dead Sea Scroll <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  '
    - name: "15: David\u2019s Child Dies"
      title: "David\u2019s Child Dies"
      number: 15
      content: "Then Nathan went to his house.And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        afflicted the child that Uriah\u2019s wife bore to David, and he became sick. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'David therefore sought God on behalf of the child. And David fasted
        and went in and lay all night on the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the elders of his house stood beside him, to raise him from the
        ground, but he would not, nor did he eat food with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "On the seventh day the child died. And the servants of David were
        afraid to tell him that the child was dead, for they said, \u201CBehold,
        while the child was yet alive, we spoke to him, and he did not listen to
        us. How then can we say to him the child is dead? He may do himself some
        harm.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But when David saw that his servants were whispering together, David
        understood that the child was dead. And David said to his servants, \u201CIs
        the child dead?\u201D They said, \u201CHe is dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then David arose from the earth and washed and anointed himself and
        changed his clothes. And he went into the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        and worshiped. He then went to his own house. And when he asked, they set
        food before him, and he ate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then his servants said to him, \u201CWhat is this thing that you
        have done? You fasted and wept for the child while he was alive; but when
        the child died, you arose and ate food.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "He said, \u201CWhile the child was still alive, I fasted and wept,
        for I said, \u2018Who knows whether the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        be gracious to me, that the child may live?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: "23: Solomon\u2019s Birth"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Birth"
      number: 23
      content: "But now he is dead. Why should I fast? Can I bring him back again?
        I shall go to him, but he will not return to me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then David comforted his wife, Bathsheba, and went in to her and
        lay with her, and she bore a son, and he called his name Solomon. And the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> loved him '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Rabbah Is Captured'
      title: Rabbah Is Captured
      number: 25
      content: 'and sent a message by Nathan the prophet. So he called his name Jedidiah,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        because of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:25 '
        content: 'means <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  Now Joab fought against Rabbah of the Ammonites and took the royal
        city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And Joab sent messengers to David and said, \u201CI have fought against
        Rabbah; moreover, I have taken the city of waters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Now then gather the rest of the people together and encamp against
        the city and take it, lest I take the city and it be called by my name.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So David gathered all the people together and went to Rabbah and
        fought against it and took it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And he took the crown of their king from his head. The weight of
        it was a talent[[COMMENT(0)]] of gold, and in it was a precious stone, and
        it was placed on David\u2019s head. And he brought out the spoil of the city,
        a very great amount. "
      comments:
      - number: '12:30 '
        content: A was about 75 pounds or 34 kilograms
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: And he brought out the people who were in it and set them to labor
        with saws and iron picks and iron axes and made them toil at[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the brick kilns. And thus he did to all the cities of the Ammonites. Then
        David and all the people returned to Jerusalem.
      comments:
      - number: '12:31 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Amnon and Tamar'
      title: Amnon and Tamar
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Absalom, David\u2019s son, had a beautiful sister, whose name
        was Tamar. And after a time Amnon, David\u2019s son, loved her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Amnon was so tormented that he made himself ill because of his
        sister Tamar, for she was a virgin, and it seemed impossible to Amnon to
        do anything to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Amnon had a friend, whose name was Jonadab, the son of Shimeah,
        David\u2019s brother. And Jonadab was a very crafty man. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CO son of the king, why are you so haggard
        morning after morning? Will you not tell me?\u201D Amnon said to him, \u201CI
        love Tamar, my brother Absalom\u2019s sister.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Jonadab said to him, \u201CLie down on your bed and pretend to be
        ill. And when your father comes to see you, say to him, \u2018Let my sister
        Tamar come and give me bread to eat, and prepare the food in my sight, that
        I may see it and eat it from her hand.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Amnon lay down and pretended to be ill. And when the king came
        to see him, Amnon said to the king, \u201CPlease let my sister Tamar come
        and make a couple of cakes in my sight, that I may eat from her hand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then David sent home to Tamar, saying, \u201CGo to your brother Amnon\u2019s
        house and prepare food for him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Tamar went to her brother Amnon\u2019s house, where he was lying
        down. And she took dough and kneaded it and made cakes in his sight and baked
        the cakes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And she took the pan and emptied it out before him, but he refused
        to eat. And Amnon said, \u201CSend out everyone from me.\u201D So everyone
        went out from him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Amnon said to Tamar, \u201CBring the food into the chamber,
        that I may eat from your hand.\u201D And Tamar took the cakes she had made
        and brought them into the chamber to Amnon her brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But when she brought them near him to eat, he took hold of her and
        said to her, \u201CCome, lie with me, my sister.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "She answered him, \u201CNo, my brother, do not violate[[COMMENT(0)]]
        me, for such a thing is not done in Israel; do not do this outrageous thing. "
      comments:
      - number: '13:12 '
        content: Or ; also verses 14, 22, 32
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "As for me, where could I carry my shame? And as for you, you would
        be as one of the outrageous fools in Israel. Now therefore, please speak
        to the king, for he will not withhold me from you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But he would not listen to her, and being stronger than she, he violated
        her and lay with her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Amnon hated her with very great hatred, so that the hatred with
        which he hated her was greater than the love with which he had loved her.
        And Amnon said to her, \u201CGet up! Go!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But she said to him, \u201CNo, my brother, for this wrong in sending
        me away is greater than the other that you did to me.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]
        But he would not listen to her. "
      comments:
      - number: '13:16 '
        content: Compare Septuagint, Vulgate; the meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He called the young man who served him and said, \u201CPut this woman
        out of my presence and bolt the door after her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now she was wearing a long robe with sleeves,[[COMMENT(0)]] for thus
        were the virgin daughters of the king dressed. So his servant put her out
        and bolted the door after her. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:18 '
        content: Or (compare Genesis 37:3); compare , verse 19
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Tamar put ashes on her head and tore the long robe that she wore.
        And she laid her hand on her head and went away, crying aloud as she went.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And her brother Absalom said to her, \u201CHas Amnon your brother
        been with you? Now hold your peace, my sister. He is your brother; do not
        take this to heart.\u201D So Tamar lived, a desolate woman, in her brother
        Absalom\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When King David heard of all these things, he was very angry.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:21 '
        content: 'Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint add '
    - name: '22: Absalom Murders Amnon'
      title: Absalom Murders Amnon
      number: 22
      content: 'But Absalom spoke to Amnon neither good nor bad, for Absalom hated
        Amnon, because he had violated his sister Tamar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "After two full years Absalom had sheepshearers at Baal-hazor, which
        is near Ephraim, and Absalom invited all the king\u2019s sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Absalom came to the king and said, \u201CBehold, your servant
        has sheepshearers. Please let the king and his servants go with your servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But the king said to Absalom, \u201CNo, my son, let us not all go,
        lest we be burdensome to you.\u201D He pressed him, but he would not go but
        gave him his blessing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Absalom said, \u201CIf not, please let my brother Amnon go with
        us.\u201D And the king said to him, \u201CWhy should he go with you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But Absalom pressed him until he let Amnon and all the king\u2019s
        sons go with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Absalom commanded his servants, \u201CMark when Amnon\u2019s
        heart is merry with wine, and when I say to you, \u2018Strike Amnon,\u2019
        then kill him. Do not fear; have I not commanded you? Be courageous and be
        valiant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So the servants of Absalom did to Amnon as Absalom had commanded.
        Then all the king\u2019s sons arose, and each mounted his mule and fled.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "While they were on the way, news came to David, \u201CAbsalom has
        struck down all the king\u2019s sons, and not one of them is left.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then the king arose and tore his garments and lay on the earth. And
        all his servants who were standing by tore their garments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "But Jonadab the son of Shimeah, David\u2019s brother, said, \u201CLet
        not my lord suppose that they have killed all the young men, the king\u2019s
        sons, for Amnon alone is dead. For by the command of Absalom this has been
        determined from the day he violated his sister Tamar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: Absalom Flees to Geshur'
      title: Absalom Flees to Geshur
      number: 33
      content: "Now therefore let not my lord the king so take it to heart as to
        suppose that all the king\u2019s sons are dead, for Amnon alone is dead.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '  But Absalom fled. And the young man who kept the watch lifted up
        his eyes and looked, and behold, many people were coming from the road behind
        him[[COMMENT(0)]] by the side of the mountain. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:34 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And Jonadab said to the king, \u201CBehold, the king\u2019s sons
        have come; as your servant said, so it has come about.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And as soon as he had finished speaking, behold, the king\u2019s
        sons came and lifted up their voice and wept. And the king also and all his
        servants wept very bitterly.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: '  But Absalom fled and went to Talmai the son of Ammihud, king of
        Geshur. And David mourned for his son day after day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'So Absalom fled and went to Geshur, and was there three years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: And the spirit of the king[[COMMENT(0)]] longed to go out to Absalom,
        because he was comforted about Amnon, since he was dead.
      comments:
      - number: '13:39 '
        content: 'Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint; Hebrew Compare Vulgate '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Absalom Returns to Jerusalem'
      title: Absalom Returns to Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Joab the son of Zeruiah knew that the king\u2019s heart went
        out to Absalom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Joab sent to Tekoa and brought from there a wise woman and said
        to her, \u201CPretend to be a mourner and put on mourning garments. Do not
        anoint yourself with oil, but behave like a woman who has been mourning many
        days for the dead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Go to the king and speak thus to him.\u201D So Joab put the words
        in her mouth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When the woman of Tekoa came to the king, she fell on her face to
        the ground and paid homage and said, \u201CSave me, O king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the king said to her, \u201CWhat is your trouble?\u201D She answered,
        \u201CAlas, I am a widow; my husband is dead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And your servant had two sons, and they quarreled with one another
        in the field. There was no one to separate them, and one struck the other
        and killed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And now the whole clan has risen against your servant, and they say,
        \u2018Give up the man who struck his brother, that we may put him to death
        for the life of his brother whom he killed.\u2019 And so they would destroy
        the heir also. Thus they would quench my coal that is left and leave to my
        husband neither name nor remnant on the face of the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the king said to the woman, \u201CGo to your house, and I will
        give orders concerning you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the woman of Tekoa said to the king, \u201COn me be the guilt,
        my lord the king, and on my father\u2019s house; let the king and his throne
        be guiltless.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The king said, \u201CIf anyone says anything to you, bring him to
        me, and he shall never touch you again.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then she said, \u201CPlease let the king invoke the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, that the avenger of blood kill no more, and my son be not destroyed.\u201D
        He said, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, not one hair of
        your son shall fall to the ground.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the woman said, \u201CPlease let your servant speak a word to
        my lord the king.\u201D He said, \u201CSpeak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the woman said, \u201CWhy then have you planned such a thing
        against the people of God? For in giving this decision the king convicts
        himself, inasmuch as the king does not bring his banished one home again. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'We must all die; we are like water spilled on the ground, which cannot
        be gathered up again. But God will not take away life, and he devises means
        so that the banished one will not remain an outcast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now I have come to say this to my lord the king because the people
        have made me afraid, and your servant thought, \u2018I will speak to the
        king; it may be that the king will perform the request of his servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "For the king will hear and deliver his servant from the hand of the
        man who would destroy me and my son together from the heritage of God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And your servant thought, \u2018The word of my lord the king will
        set me at rest,\u2019 for my lord the king is like the angel of God to discern
        good and evil. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God be with you!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the king answered the woman, \u201CDo not hide from me anything
        I ask you.\u201D And the woman said, \u201CLet my lord the king speak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The king said, \u201CIs the hand of Joab with you in all this?\u201D
        The woman answered and said, \u201CAs surely as you live, my lord the king,
        one cannot turn to the right hand or to the left from anything that my lord
        the king has said. It was your servant Joab who commanded me; it was he who
        put all these words in the mouth of your servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "In order to change the course of things your servant Joab did this.
        But my lord has wisdom like the wisdom of the angel of God to know all things
        that are on the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then the king said to Joab, \u201CBehold now, I grant this; go, bring
        back the young man Absalom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Joab fell on his face to the ground and paid homage and blessed
        the king. And Joab said, \u201CToday your servant knows that I have found
        favor in your sight, my lord the king, in that the king has granted the request
        of his servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So Joab arose and went to Geshur and brought Absalom to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the king said, \u201CLet him dwell apart in his own house; he
        is not to come into my presence.\u201D So Absalom lived apart in his own
        house and did not come into the king\u2019s presence.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now in all Israel there was no one so much to be praised for his
        handsome appearance as Absalom. From the sole of his foot to the crown of
        his head there was no blemish in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And when he cut the hair of his head (for at the end of every year
        he used to cut it; when it was heavy on him, he cut it), he weighed the hair
        of his head, two hundred shekels[[COMMENT(0)]] by the king\u2019s weight. "
      comments:
      - number: '14:26 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'There were born to Absalom three sons, and one daughter whose name
        was Tamar. She was a beautiful woman.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So Absalom lived two full years in Jerusalem, without coming into
        the king\u2019s presence. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Absalom sent for Joab, to send him to the king, but Joab would
        not come to him. And he sent a second time, but Joab would not come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then he said to his servants, \u201CSee, Joab\u2019s field is next
        to mine, and he has barley there; go and set it on fire.\u201D So Absalom\u2019s
        servants set the field on fire.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:30 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Dead Sea Scroll add '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Joab arose and went to Absalom at his house and said to him,
        \u201CWhy have your servants set my field on fire?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Absalom answered Joab, \u201CBehold, I sent word to you, \u2018Come
        here, that I may send you to the king, to ask, \u201CWhy have I come from
        Geshur? It would be better for me to be there still.\u201D Now therefore
        let me go into the presence of the king, and if there is guilt in me, let
        him put me to death.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Then Joab went to the king and told him, and he summoned Absalom.
        So he came to the king and bowed himself on his face to the ground before
        the king, and the king kissed Absalom.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Absalom\u2019s Conspiracy"
      title: "Absalom\u2019s Conspiracy"
      number: 1
      content: '  After this Absalom got himself a chariot and horses, and fifty
        men to run before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Absalom used to rise early and stand beside the way of the gate.
        And when any man had a dispute to come before the king for judgment, Absalom
        would call to him and say, \u201CFrom what city are you?\u201D And when he
        said, \u201CYour servant is of such and such a tribe in Israel,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Absalom would say to him, \u201CSee, your claims are good and right,
        but there is no man designated by the king to hear you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Absalom would say, \u201COh that I were judge in the land! Then
        every man with a dispute or cause might come to me, and I would give him
        justice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And whenever a man came near to pay homage to him, he would put out
        his hand and take hold of him and kiss him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Thus Absalom did to all of Israel who came to the king for judgment.
        So Absalom stole the hearts of the men of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And at the end of four[[COMMENT(0)]] years Absalom said to the king,
        \u201CPlease let me go and pay my vow, which I have vowed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        in Hebron. "
      comments:
      - number: '15:7 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac; Hebrew '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For your servant vowed a vow while I lived at Geshur in Aram, saying,
        \u2018If the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will indeed bring me back to Jerusalem,
        then I will offer worship to[[COMMENT(0)]] the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '15:8 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The king said to him, \u201CGo in peace.\u201D So he arose and went
        to Hebron. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Absalom sent secret messengers throughout all the tribes of Israel,
        saying, \u201CAs soon as you hear the sound of the trumpet, then say, \u2018Absalom
        is king at Hebron!\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'With Absalom went two hundred men from Jerusalem who were invited
        guests, and they went in their innocence and knew nothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: David Flees Jerusalem'
      title: David Flees Jerusalem
      number: 12
      content: "And while Absalom was offering the sacrifices, he sent for[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        Ahithophel the Gilonite, David\u2019s counselor, from his city Giloh. And
        the conspiracy grew strong, and the people with Absalom kept increasing.  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:12 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And a messenger came to David, saying, \u201CThe hearts of the men
        of Israel have gone after Absalom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then David said to all his servants who were with him at Jerusalem,
        \u201CArise, and let us flee, or else there will be no escape for us from
        Absalom. Go quickly, lest he overtake us quickly and bring down ruin on us
        and strike the city with the edge of the sword.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And the king\u2019s servants said to the king, \u201CBehold, your
        servants are ready to do whatever my lord the king decides.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So the king went out, and all his household after him. And the king
        left ten concubines to keep the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the king went out, and all the people after him. And they halted
        at the last house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And all his servants passed by him, and all the Cherethites, and
        all the Pelethites, and all the six hundred Gittites who had followed him
        from Gath, passed on before the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the king said to Ittai the Gittite, \u201CWhy do you also go
        with us? Go back and stay with the king, for you are a foreigner and also
        an exile from your home. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "You came only yesterday, and shall I today make you wander about
        with us, since I go I know not where? Go back and take your brothers with
        you, and may the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> show[[COMMENT(0)]] steadfast
        love and faithfulness to you.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '15:20 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew lacks <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But Ittai answered the king, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives, and as my lord the king lives, wherever my lord the king shall be,
        whether for death or for life, there also will your servant be.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And David said to Ittai, \u201CGo then, pass on.\u201D So Ittai the
        Gittite passed on with all his men and all the little ones who were with
        him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And all the land wept aloud as all the people passed by, and the
        king crossed the brook Kidron, and all the people passed on toward the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And Abiathar came up, and behold, Zadok came also with all the Levites,
        bearing the ark of the covenant of God. And they set down the ark of God
        until the people had all passed out of the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then the king said to Zadok, \u201CCarry the ark of God back into
        the city. If I find favor in the eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        he will bring me back and let me see both it and his dwelling place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But if he says, \u2018I have no pleasure in you,\u2019 behold, here
        I am, let him do to me what seems good to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The king also said to Zadok the priest, \u201CAre you not a seer?
        Go back[[COMMENT(0)]] to the city in peace, with your two sons, Ahimaaz your
        son, and Jonathan the son of Abiathar. "
      comments:
      - number: '15:27 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "See, I will wait at the fords of the wilderness until word comes
        from you to inform me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So Zadok and Abiathar carried the ark of God back to Jerusalem, and
        they remained there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But David went up the ascent of the Mount of Olives, weeping as he
        went, barefoot and with his head covered. And all the people who were with
        him covered their heads, and they went up, weeping as they went. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And it was told David, \u201CAhithophel is among the conspirators
        with Absalom.\u201D And David said, \u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        please turn the counsel of Ahithophel into foolishness.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'While David was coming to the summit, where God was worshiped, behold,
        Hushai the Archite came to meet him with his coat torn and dirt on his head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "David said to him, \u201CIf you go on with me, you will be a burden
        to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But if you return to the city and say to Absalom, \u2018I will be
        your servant, O king; as I have been your father\u2019s servant in time past,
        so now I will be your servant,\u2019 then you will defeat for me the counsel
        of Ahithophel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Are not Zadok and Abiathar the priests with you there? So whatever
        you hear from the king\u2019s house, tell it to Zadok and Abiathar the priests. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Behold, their two sons are with them there, Ahimaaz, Zadok\u2019s
        son, and Jonathan, Abiathar\u2019s son, and by them you shall send to me
        everything you hear.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "So Hushai, David\u2019s friend, came into the city, just as Absalom
        was entering Jerusalem."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David and Ziba'
      title: David and Ziba
      number: 1
      content: '  When David had passed a little beyond the summit, Ziba the servant
        of Mephibosheth met him, with a couple of donkeys saddled, bearing two hundred
        loaves of bread, a hundred bunches of raisins, a hundred of summer fruits,
        and a skin of wine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the king said to Ziba, \u201CWhy have you brought these?\u201D
        Ziba answered, \u201CThe donkeys are for the king\u2019s household to ride
        on, the bread and summer fruit for the young men to eat, and the wine for
        those who faint in the wilderness to drink.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the king said, \u201CAnd where is your master\u2019s son?\u201D
        Ziba said to the king, \u201CBehold, he remains in Jerusalem, for he said,
        \u2018Today the house of Israel will give me back the kingdom of my father.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Shimei Curses David'
      title: Shimei Curses David
      number: 4
      content: "Then the king said to Ziba, \u201CBehold, all that belonged to Mephibosheth
        is now yours.\u201D And Ziba said, \u201CI pay homage; let me ever find favor
        in your sight, my lord the king.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When King David came to Bahurim, there came out a man of the family
        of the house of Saul, whose name was Shimei, the son of Gera, and as he came
        he cursed continually. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he threw stones at David and at all the servants of King David,
        and all the people and all the mighty men were on his right hand and on his
        left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Shimei said as he cursed, \u201CGet out, get out, you man of
        blood, you worthless man! "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  has avenged on you all the blood
        of the house of Saul, in whose place you have reigned, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has given the kingdom into the hand of your son Absalom. See, your evil is
        on you, for you are a man of blood.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Abishai the son of Zeruiah said to the king, \u201CWhy should
        this dead dog curse my lord the king? Let me go over and take off his head.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But the king said, \u201CWhat have I to do with you, you sons of
        Zeruiah? If he is cursing because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has said
        to him, \u2018Curse David,\u2019 who then shall say, \u2018Why have you done
        so?\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And David said to Abishai and to all his servants, \u201CBehold,
        my own son seeks my life; how much more now may this Benjaminite! Leave him
        alone, and let him curse, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has told him
        to. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "It may be that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will look on the wrong
        done to me,[[COMMENT(0)]] and that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will repay
        me with good for his cursing today.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '16:12 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Vulgate '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So David and his men went on the road, while Shimei went along on
        the hillside opposite him and cursed as he went and threw stones at him and
        flung dust. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Absalom Enters Jerusalem'
      title: Absalom Enters Jerusalem
      number: 14
      content: 'And the king, and all the people who were with him, arrived weary
        at the Jordan.[[COMMENT(0)]] And there he refreshed himself.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:14 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Now Absalom and all the people, the men of Israel, came to Jerusalem,
        and Ahithophel with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And when Hushai the Archite, David\u2019s friend, came to Absalom,
        Hushai said to Absalom, \u201CLong live the king! Long live the king!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Absalom said to Hushai, \u201CIs this your loyalty to your friend?
        Why did you not go with your friend?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Hushai said to Absalom, \u201CNo, for whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and this people and all the men of Israel have chosen, his I will be, and
        with him I will remain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And again, whom should I serve? Should it not be his son? As I have
        served your father, so I will serve you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Absalom said to Ahithophel, \u201CGive your counsel. What shall
        we do?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Ahithophel said to Absalom, \u201CGo in to your father\u2019s concubines,
        whom he has left to keep the house, and all Israel will hear that you have
        made yourself a stench to your father, and the hands of all who are with
        you will be strengthened.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So they pitched a tent for Absalom on the roof. And Absalom went
        in to his father\u2019s concubines in the sight of all Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Now in those days the counsel that Ahithophel gave was as if one consulted
        the word of God; so was all the counsel of Ahithophel esteemed, both by David
        and by Absalom.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hushai Saves David'
      title: Hushai Saves David
      number: 1
      content: "  Moreover, Ahithophel said to Absalom, \u201CLet me choose twelve
        thousand men, and I will arise and pursue David tonight. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I will come upon him while he is weary and discouraged and throw
        him into a panic, and all the people who are with him will flee. I will strike
        down only the king, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and I will bring all the people back to you as a bride comes home
        to her husband. You seek the life of only one man,[[COMMENT(0)]] and all
        the people will be at peace.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '17:3 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the advice seemed right in the eyes of Absalom and all the elders
        of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Absalom said, \u201CCall Hushai the Archite also, and let us
        hear what he has to say.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And when Hushai came to Absalom, Absalom said to him, \u201CThus
        has Ahithophel spoken; shall we do as he says? If not, you speak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Hushai said to Absalom, \u201CThis time the counsel that Ahithophel
        has given is not good.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Hushai said, \u201CYou know that your father and his men are mighty
        men, and that they are enraged,[[COMMENT(0)]]  like a bear robbed of her
        cubs in the field. Besides, your father is expert in war; he will not spend
        the night with the people. "
      comments:
      - number: '17:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Behold, even now he has hidden himself in one of the pits or in some
        other place. And as soon as some of the people fall[[COMMENT(0)]] at the
        first attack, whoever hears it will say, \u2018There has been a slaughter
        among the people who follow Absalom.\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '17:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then even the valiant man, whose heart is like the heart of a lion,
        will utterly melt with fear, for all Israel knows that your father is a mighty
        man, and that those who are with him are valiant men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But my counsel is that all Israel be gathered to you, from Dan to
        Beersheba, as the sand by the sea for multitude, and that you go to battle
        in person. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So we shall come upon him in some place where he is to be found,
        and we shall light upon him as the dew falls on the ground, and of him and
        all the men with him not one will be left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "If he withdraws into a city, then all Israel will bring ropes to
        that city, and we shall drag it into the valley, until not even a pebble
        is to be found there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Absalom and all the men of Israel said, \u201CThe counsel of
        Hushai the Archite is better than the counsel of Ahithophel.\u201D For the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had ordained[[COMMENT(0)]] to defeat the good
        counsel of Ahithophel, so that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> might bring
        harm upon Absalom.  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:14 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  Then Hushai said to Zadok and Abiathar the priests, \u201CThus
        and so did Ahithophel counsel Absalom and the elders of Israel, and thus
        and so have I counseled. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now therefore send quickly and tell David, \u2018Do not stay tonight
        at the fords of the wilderness, but by all means pass over, lest the king
        and all the people who are with him be swallowed up.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now Jonathan and Ahimaaz were waiting at En-rogel. A female servant
        was to go and tell them, and they were to go and tell King David, for they
        were not to be seen entering the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But a young man saw them and told Absalom. So both of them went away
        quickly and came to the house of a man at Bahurim, who had a well in his
        courtyard. And they went down into it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And the woman took and spread a covering over the well\u2019s mouth
        and scattered grain on it, and nothing was known of it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "When Absalom\u2019s servants came to the woman at the house, they
        said, \u201CWhere are Ahimaaz and Jonathan?\u201D And the woman said to them,
        \u201CThey have gone over the brook[[COMMENT(0)]] of water.\u201D And when
        they had sought and could not find them, they returned to Jerusalem.  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:20 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "After they had gone, the men came up out of the well, and went and
        told King David. They said to David, \u201CArise, and go quickly over the
        water, for thus and so has Ahithophel counseled against you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then David arose, and all the people who were with him, and they
        crossed the Jordan. By daybreak not one was left who had not crossed the
        Jordan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When Ahithophel saw that his counsel was not followed, he saddled
        his donkey and went off home to his own city. He set his house in order and
        hanged himself, and he died and was buried in the tomb of his father.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then David came to Mahanaim. And Absalom crossed the Jordan with
        all the men of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now Absalom had set Amasa over the army instead of Joab. Amasa was
        the son of a man named Ithra the Ishmaelite,[[COMMENT(0)]] who had married
        Abigal the daughter of Nahash, sister of Zeruiah, Joab\u2019s mother. "
      comments:
      - number: '17:25 '
        content: 'Compare 1 Chronicles 2:17; Hebrew '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Israel and Absalom encamped in the land of Gilead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When David came to Mahanaim, Shobi the son of Nahash from Rabbah
        of the Ammonites, and Machir the son of Ammiel from Lo-debar, and Barzillai
        the Gileadite from Rogelim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'brought beds, basins, and earthen vessels, wheat, barley, flour,
        parched grain, beans and lentils,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:28 '
        content: 'Hebrew adds '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "honey and curds and sheep and cheese from the herd, for David and
        the people with him to eat, for they said, \u201CThe people are hungry and
        weary and thirsty in the wilderness.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Absalom Killed'
      title: Absalom Killed
      number: 1
      content: '  Then David mustered the men who were with him and set over them
        commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And David sent out the army, one third under the command of Joab,
        one third under the command of Abishai the son of Zeruiah, Joab\u2019s brother,
        and one third under the command of Ittai the Gittite. And the king said to
        the men, \u201CI myself will also go out with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But the men said, \u201CYou shall not go out. For if we flee, they
        will not care about us. If half of us die, they will not care about us. But
        you are worth ten thousand of us. Therefore it is better that you send us
        help from the city.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The king said to them, \u201CWhatever seems best to you I will do.\u201D
        So the king stood at the side of the gate, while all the army marched out
        by hundreds and by thousands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the king ordered Joab and Abishai and Ittai, \u201CDeal gently
        for my sake with the young man Absalom.\u201D And all the people heard when
        the king gave orders to all the commanders about Absalom.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So the army went out into the field against Israel, and the battle
        was fought in the forest of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the men of Israel were defeated there by the servants of David,
        and the loss there was great on that day, twenty thousand men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The battle spread over the face of all the country, and the forest
        devoured more people that day than the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Absalom happened to meet the servants of David. Absalom was riding
        on his mule, and the mule went under the thick branches of a great oak,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        and his head caught fast in the oak, and he was suspended between heaven
        and earth, while the mule that was under him went on. '
      comments:
      - number: '18:9 '
        content: Or ; also verses 10, 14
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And a certain man saw it and told Joab, \u201CBehold, I saw Absalom
        hanging in an oak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Joab said to the man who told him, \u201CWhat, you saw him! Why then
        did you not strike him there to the ground? I would have been glad to give
        you ten pieces of silver and a belt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But the man said to Joab, \u201CEven if I felt in my hand the weight
        of a thousand pieces of silver, I would not reach out my hand against the
        king\u2019s son, for in our hearing the king commanded you and Abishai and
        Ittai, \u2018For my sake protect the young man Absalom.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "On the other hand, if I had dealt treacherously against his life[[COMMENT(0)]]
        (and there is nothing hidden from the king), then you yourself would have
        stood aloof.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '18:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Joab said, \u201CI will not waste time like this with you.\u201D
        And he took three javelins in his hand and thrust them into the heart of
        Absalom while he was still alive in the oak. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And ten young men, Joab\u2019s armor-bearers, surrounded Absalom
        and struck him and killed him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Joab blew the trumpet, and the troops came back from pursuing
        Israel, for Joab restrained them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And they took Absalom and threw him into a great pit in the forest
        and raised over him a very great heap of stones. And all Israel fled every
        one to his own home. '
      comments: []
    - name: "18: David Hears of Absalom\u2019s Death"
      title: "David Hears of Absalom\u2019s Death"
      number: 18
      content: "Now Absalom in his lifetime had taken and set up for himself the
        pillar that is in the King\u2019s Valley, for he said, \u201CI have no son
        to keep my name in remembrance.\u201D He called the pillar after his own
        name, and it is called Absalom\u2019s monument[[COMMENT(0)]] to this day.  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:18 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Ahimaaz the son of Zadok said, \u201CLet me run and carry news
        to the king that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has delivered him from the
        hand of his enemies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Joab said to him, \u201CYou are not to carry news today. You
        may carry news another day, but today you shall carry no news, because the
        king\u2019s son is dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Joab said to the Cushite, \u201CGo, tell the king what you have
        seen.\u201D The Cushite bowed before Joab, and ran. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Ahimaaz the son of Zadok said again to Joab, \u201CCome what
        may, let me also run after the Cushite.\u201D And Joab said, \u201CWhy will
        you run, my son, seeing that you will have no reward for the news?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CCome what may,\u201D he said, \u201CI will run.\u201D So he
        said to him, \u201CRun.\u201D Then Ahimaaz ran by the way of the plain, and
        outran the Cushite.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now David was sitting between the two gates, and the watchman went
        up to the roof of the gate by the wall, and when he lifted up his eyes and
        looked, he saw a man running alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The watchman called out and told the king. And the king said, \u201CIf
        he is alone, there is news in his mouth.\u201D And he drew nearer and nearer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "The watchman saw another man running. And the watchman called to
        the gate and said, \u201CSee, another man running alone!\u201D The king said,
        \u201CHe also brings news.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The watchman said, \u201CI think the running of the first is like
        the running of Ahimaaz the son of Zadok.\u201D And the king said, \u201CHe
        is a good man and comes with good news.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Ahimaaz cried out to the king, \u201CAll is well.\u201D And
        he bowed before the king with his face to the earth and said, \u201CBlessed
        be the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, who has delivered up the men
        who raised their hand against my lord the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And the king said, \u201CIs it well with the young man Absalom?\u201D
        Ahimaaz answered, \u201CWhen Joab sent the king\u2019s servant, your servant,
        I saw a great commotion, but I do not know what it was.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "30: David\u2019s Grief"
      title: "David\u2019s Grief"
      number: 30
      content: "And the king said, \u201CTurn aside and stand here.\u201D So he turned
        aside and stood still.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And behold, the Cushite came, and the Cushite said, \u201CGood news
        for my lord the king! For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has delivered you
        this day from the hand of all who rose up against you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "The king said to the Cushite, \u201CIs it well with the young man
        Absalom?\u201D And the Cushite answered, \u201CMay the enemies of my lord
        the king and all who rise up against you for evil be like that young man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "[[COMMENT(0)]] And the king was deeply moved and went up to the chamber
        over the gate and wept. And as he went, he said, \u201CO my son Absalom,
        my son, my son Absalom! Would I had died instead of you, O Absalom, my son,
        my son!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '18:33 '
        content: Ch 19:1 in Hebrew
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joab Rebukes David'
      title: Joab Rebukes David
      number: 1
      content: "  It was told Joab, \u201CBehold, the king is weeping and mourning
        for Absalom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So the victory that day was turned into mourning for all the people,
        for the people heard that day, \u201CThe king is grieving for his son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the people stole into the city that day as people steal in who
        are ashamed when they flee in battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The king covered his face, and the king cried with a loud voice,
        \u201CO my son Absalom, O Absalom, my son, my son!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Joab came into the house to the king and said, \u201CYou have
        today covered with shame the faces of all your servants, who have this day
        saved your life and the lives of your sons and your daughters and the lives
        of your wives and your concubines, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'because you love those who hate you and hate those who love you.
        For you have made it clear today that commanders and servants are nothing
        to you, for today I know that if Absalom were alive and all of us were dead
        today, then you would be pleased. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now therefore arise, go out and speak kindly to your servants, for
        I swear by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, if you do not go, not a man will
        stay with you this night, and this will be worse for you than all the evil
        that has come upon you from your youth until now.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: David Returns to Jerusalem'
      title: David Returns to Jerusalem
      number: 8
      content: "Then the king arose and took his seat in the gate. And the people
        were all told, \u201CBehold, the king is sitting in the gate.\u201D And all
        the people came before the king.Now Israel had fled every man to his own
        home. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And all the people were arguing throughout all the tribes of Israel,
        saying, \u201CThe king delivered us from the hand of our enemies and saved
        us from the hand of the Philistines, and now he has fled out of the land
        from Absalom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Absalom, whom we anointed over us, is dead in battle. Now therefore
        why do you say nothing about bringing the king back?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And King David sent this message to Zadok and Abiathar the priests:
        \u201CSay to the elders of Judah, \u2018Why should you be the last to bring
        the king back to his house, when the word of all Israel has come to the king?[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:11 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "You are my brothers; you are my bone and my flesh. Why then should
        you be the last to bring back the king?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And say to Amasa, \u2018Are you not my bone and my flesh? God do
        so to me and more also, if you are not commander of my army from now on in
        place of Joab.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And he swayed the heart of all the men of Judah as one man, so that
        they sent word to the king, \u201CReturn, both you and all your servants.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: David Pardons His Enemies'
      title: David Pardons His Enemies
      number: 15
      content: 'So the king came back to the Jordan, and Judah came to Gilgal to
        meet the king and to bring the king over the Jordan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Shimei the son of Gera, the Benjaminite, from Bahurim, hurried
        to come down with the men of Judah to meet King David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And with him were a thousand men from Benjamin. And Ziba the servant
        of the house of Saul, with his fifteen sons and his twenty servants, rushed
        down to the Jordan before the king, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and they crossed the ford to bring over the king\u2019s household
        and to do his pleasure. And Shimei the son of Gera fell down before the king,
        as he was about to cross the Jordan, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and said to the king, \u201CLet not my lord hold me guilty or remember
        how your servant did wrong on the day my lord the king left Jerusalem. Do
        not let the king take it to heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For your servant knows that I have sinned. Therefore, behold, I have
        come this day, the first of all the house of Joseph to come down to meet
        my lord the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Abishai the son of Zeruiah answered, \u201CShall not Shimei be put
        to death for this, because he cursed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        anointed?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But David said, \u201CWhat have I to do with you, you sons of Zeruiah,
        that you should this day be as an adversary to me? Shall anyone be put to
        death in Israel this day? For do I not know that I am this day king over
        Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And the king said to Shimei, \u201CYou shall not die.\u201D And the
        king gave him his oath.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And Mephibosheth the son of Saul came down to meet the king. He had
        neither taken care of his feet nor trimmed his beard nor washed his clothes,
        from the day the king departed until the day he came back in safety. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And when he came to Jerusalem to meet the king, the king said to
        him, \u201CWhy did you not go with me, Mephibosheth?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "He answered, \u201CMy lord, O king, my servant deceived me, for your
        servant said to him, \u2018I will saddle a donkey for myself,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        that I may ride on it and go with the king.\u2019 For your servant is lame. "
      comments:
      - number: '19:26 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He has slandered your servant to my lord the king. But my lord the
        king is like the angel of God; do therefore what seems good to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "For all my father\u2019s house were but men doomed to death before
        my lord the king, but you set your servant among those who eat at your table.
        What further right have I, then, to cry to the king?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And the king said to him, \u201CWhy speak any more of your affairs?
        I have decided: you and Ziba shall divide the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And Mephibosheth said to the king, \u201COh, let him take it all,
        since my lord the king has come safely home.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now Barzillai the Gileadite had come down from Rogelim, and he went
        on with the king to the Jordan, to escort him over the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Barzillai was a very aged man, eighty years old. He had provided
        the king with food while he stayed at Mahanaim, for he was a very wealthy
        man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And the king said to Barzillai, \u201CCome over with me, and I will
        provide for you with me in Jerusalem.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But Barzillai said to the king, \u201CHow many years have I still
        to live, that I should go up with the king to Jerusalem? "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'I am this day eighty years old. Can I discern what is pleasant and
        what is not? Can your servant taste what he eats or what he drinks? Can I
        still listen to the voice of singing men and singing women? Why then should
        your servant be an added burden to my lord the king? '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Your servant will go a little way over the Jordan with the king.
        Why should the king repay me with such a reward? '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Please let your servant return, that I may die in my own city near
        the grave of my father and my mother. But here is your servant Chimham. Let
        him go over with my lord the king, and do for him whatever seems good to
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And the king answered, \u201CChimham shall go over with me, and I
        will do for him whatever seems good to you, and all that you desire of me
        I will do for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Then all the people went over the Jordan, and the king went over.
        And the king kissed Barzillai and blessed him, and he returned to his own
        home. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'The king went on to Gilgal, and Chimham went on with him. All the
        people of Judah, and also half the people of Israel, brought the king on
        his way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Then all the men of Israel came to the king and said to the king,
        \u201CWhy have our brothers the men of Judah stolen you away and brought
        the king and his household over the Jordan, and all David\u2019s men with
        him?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "All the men of Judah answered the men of Israel, \u201CBecause the
        king is our close relative. Why then are you angry over this matter? Have
        we eaten at all at the king\u2019s expense? Or has he given us any gift?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "And the men of Israel answered the men of Judah, \u201CWe have ten
        shares in the king, and in David also we have more than you. Why then did
        you despise us? Were we not the first to speak of bringing back our king?\u201D
        But the words of the men of Judah were fiercer than the words of the men
        of Israel."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Rebellion of Sheba'
      title: The Rebellion of Sheba
      number: 1
      content: "  Now there happened to be there a worthless man, whose name was
        Sheba, the son of Bichri, a Benjaminite. And he blew the trumpet and said, 
        \u201CWe have no portion in David,and we have no inheritance in the son of
        Jesse;  every man to his tents, O Israel!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So all the men of Israel withdrew from David and followed Sheba the
        son of Bichri. But the men of Judah followed their king steadfastly from
        the Jordan to Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And David came to his house at Jerusalem. And the king took the ten
        concubines whom he had left to care for the house and put them in a house
        under guard and provided for them, but did not go in to them. So they were
        shut up until the day of their death, living as if in widowhood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the king said to Amasa, \u201CCall the men of Judah together
        to me within three days, and be here yourself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So Amasa went to summon Judah, but he delayed beyond the set time
        that had been appointed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And David said to Abishai, \u201CNow Sheba the son of Bichri will
        do us more harm than Absalom. Take your lord\u2019s servants and pursue him,
        lest he get himself to fortified cities and escape from us.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And there went out after him Joab\u2019s men and the Cherethites
        and the Pelethites, and all the mighty men. They went out from Jerusalem
        to pursue Sheba the son of Bichri. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "When they were at the great stone that is in Gibeon, Amasa came to
        meet them. Now Joab was wearing a soldier\u2019s garment, and over it was
        a belt with a sword in its sheath fastened on his thigh, and as he went forward
        it fell out. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Joab said to Amasa, \u201CIs it well with you, my brother?\u201D
        And Joab took Amasa by the beard with his right hand to kiss him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Amasa did not observe the sword that was in Joab\u2019s hand.
        So Joab struck him with it in the stomach and spilled his entrails to the
        ground without striking a second blow, and he died.Then Joab and Abishai
        his brother pursued Sheba the son of Bichri. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And one of Joab\u2019s young men took his stand by Amasa and said,
        \u201CWhoever favors Joab, and whoever is for David, let him follow Joab.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Amasa lay wallowing in his blood in the highway. And anyone who
        came by, seeing him, stopped. And when the man saw that all the people stopped,
        he carried Amasa out of the highway into the field and threw a garment over
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When he was taken out of the highway, all the people went on after
        Joab to pursue Sheba the son of Bichri.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Sheba passed through all the tribes of Israel to Abel of Beth-maacah,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and all the Bichrites assembled and followed him in. '
      comments:
      - number: '20:14 '
        content: 'Compare 20:15; Hebrew Hebrew '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And all the men who were with Joab came and besieged him in Abel
        of Beth-maacah. They cast up a mound against the city, and it stood against
        the rampart, and they were battering the wall to throw it down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then a wise woman called from the city, \u201CListen! Listen! Tell
        Joab, \u2018Come here, that I may speak to you.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he came near her, and the woman said, \u201CAre you Joab?\u201D
        He answered, \u201CI am.\u201D Then she said to him, \u201CListen to the
        words of your servant.\u201D And he answered, \u201CI am listening.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then she said, \u201CThey used to say in former times, \u2018Let
        them but ask counsel at Abel,\u2019 and so they settled a matter. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "I am one of those who are peaceable and faithful in Israel. You seek
        to destroy a city that is a mother in Israel. Why will you swallow up the
        heritage of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Joab answered, \u201CFar be it from me, far be it, that I should
        swallow up or destroy! "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "That is not true. But a man of the hill country of Ephraim, called
        Sheba the son of Bichri, has lifted up his hand against King David. Give
        up him alone, and I will withdraw from the city.\u201D And the woman said
        to Joab, \u201CBehold, his head shall be thrown to you over the wall.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then the woman went to all the people in her wisdom. And they cut
        off the head of Sheba the son of Bichri and threw it out to Joab. So he blew
        the trumpet, and they dispersed from the city, every man to his home. And
        Joab returned to Jerusalem to the king.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Now Joab was in command of all the army of Israel; and Benaiah
        the son of Jehoiada was in command of the Cherethites and the Pelethites; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and Adoram was in charge of the forced labor; and Jehoshaphat the
        son of Ahilud was the recorder; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'and Sheva was secretary; and Zadok and Abiathar were priests; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "and Ira the Jairite was also David\u2019s priest."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Avenges the Gibeonites'
      title: David Avenges the Gibeonites
      number: 1
      content: "  Now there was a famine in the days of David for three years, year
        after year. And David sought the face of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CThere is bloodguilt on Saul
        and on his house, because he put the Gibeonites to death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So the king called the Gibeonites and spoke to them. Now the Gibeonites
        were not of the people of Israel but of the remnant of the Amorites. Although
        the people of Israel had sworn to spare them, Saul had sought to strike them
        down in his zeal for the people of Israel and Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And David said to the Gibeonites, \u201CWhat shall I do for you?
        And how shall I make atonement, that you may bless the heritage of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The Gibeonites said to him, \u201CIt is not a matter of silver or
        gold between us and Saul or his house; neither is it for us to put any man
        to death in Israel.\u201D And he said, \u201CWhat do you say that I shall
        do for you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They said to the king, \u201CThe man who consumed us and planned
        to destroy us, so that we should have no place in all the territory of Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "let seven of his sons be given to us, so that we may hang them before
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> at Gibeah of Saul, the chosen of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D
        And the king said, \u201CI will give them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But the king spared Mephibosheth, the son of Saul\u2019s son Jonathan,
        because of the oath of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that was between them,
        between David and Jonathan the son of Saul. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The king took the two sons of Rizpah the daughter of Aiah, whom she
        bore to Saul, Armoni and Mephibosheth; and the five sons of Merab[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the daughter of Saul, whom she bore to Adriel the son of Barzillai the Meholathite; '
      comments:
      - number: '21:8 '
        content: 'Two Hebrew manuscripts, Septuagint; most Hebrew manuscripts '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and he gave them into the hands of the Gibeonites, and they hanged
        them on the mountain before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and the seven
        of them perished together. They were put to death in the first days of harvest,
        at the beginning of barley harvest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Then Rizpah the daughter of Aiah took sackcloth and spread it for
        herself on the rock, from the beginning of harvest until rain fell upon them
        from the heavens. And she did not allow the birds of the air to come upon
        them by day, or the beasts of the field by night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When David was told what Rizpah the daughter of Aiah, the concubine
        of Saul, had done, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'David went and took the bones of Saul and the bones of his son Jonathan
        from the men of Jabesh-gilead, who had stolen them from the public square
        of Beth-shan, where the Philistines had hanged them, on the day the Philistines
        killed Saul on Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he brought up from there the bones of Saul and the bones of his
        son Jonathan; and they gathered the bones of those who were hanged. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: War with the Philistines'
      title: War with the Philistines
      number: 14
      content: 'And they buried the bones of Saul and his son Jonathan in the land
        of Benjamin in Zela, in the tomb of Kish his father. And they did all that
        the king commanded. And after that God responded to the plea for the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'There was war again between the Philistines and Israel, and David
        went down together with his servants, and they fought against the Philistines.
        And David grew weary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Ishbi-benob, one of the descendants of the giants, whose spear
        weighed three hundred shekels[[COMMENT(0)]] of bronze, and who was armed
        with a new sword, thought to kill David. '
      comments:
      - number: '21:16 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But Abishai the son of Zeruiah came to his aid and attacked the Philistine
        and killed him. Then David\u2019s men swore to him, \u201CYou shall no longer
        go out with us to battle, lest you quench the lamp of Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  After this there was again war with the Philistines at Gob. Then
        Sibbecai the Hushathite struck down Saph, who was one of the descendants
        of the giants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And there was again war with the Philistines at Gob, and Elhanan
        the son of Jaare-oregim, the Bethlehemite, struck down Goliath the Gittite,
        the shaft of whose spear was like a weaver\u2019s beam.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:19 '
        content: Contrast 1 Chronicles 20:5, which may preserve the original reading
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And there was again war at Gath, where there was a man of great stature,
        who had six fingers on each hand, and six toes on each foot, twenty-four
        in number, and he also was descended from the giants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And when he taunted Israel, Jonathan the son of Shimei, David\u2019s
        brother, struck him down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: These four were descended from the giants in Gath, and they fell by
        the hand of David and by the hand of his servants.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Song of Deliverance"
      title: "David\u2019s Song of Deliverance"
      number: 1
      content: '  And David spoke to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> the words of
        this song on the day when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> delivered him from
        the hand of all his enemies, and from the hand of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He said,  \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is my rock and my
        fortress and my deliverer,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  my[[COMMENT(0)]] God, my rock, in whom I take refuge,  my shield,
        and the horn of my salvation,  my stronghold and my refuge,my savior; you
        save me from violence.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:3 '
        content: 'Septuagint (compare Psalm 18:2); Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I call upon the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who is worthy to be
        praised,and I am saved from my enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  \u201CFor the waves of death encompassed me,the torrents of destruction
        assailed me;[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  the cords of Sheol entangled me;the snares of death confronted
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  \u201CIn my distress I called upon the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;to
        my God I called.From his temple he heard my voice,and my cry came to his
        ears.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CThen the earth reeled and rocked;  the foundations of the heavens
        trembledand quaked, because he was angry.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Smoke went up from his nostrils,[[COMMENT(0)]]and devouring fire
        from his mouth;  glowing coals flamed forth from him.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  He bowed the heavens and came down;  thick darkness was under his
        feet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He rode on a cherub and flew;he was seen on the wings of the wind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He made darkness around him his canopy,thick clouds, a gathering
        of water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Out of the brightness before him  coals of fire flamed forth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> thundered from heaven,and the Most
        High uttered his voice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he sent out arrows and scattered them;lightning, and routed them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the channels of the sea were seen;the foundations of the world
        were laid bare,at the rebuke of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,at the blast
        of the breath of his nostrils.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  \u201CHe sent from on high, he took me;he drew me out of many waters.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He rescued me from my strong enemy,from those who hated me,for they
        were too mighty for me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'They confronted me in the day of my calamity,but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was my support.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  He brought me out into a broad place;he rescued me, because he
        delighted in me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  dealt with me according to
        my righteousness;according to the cleanness of my hands he rewarded me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  For I have kept the ways of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and
        have not wickedly departed from my God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  For all his rules were before me,and from his statutes I did not
        turn aside.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'I was blameless before him,and I kept myself from guilt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has rewarded me according to
        my righteousness,according to my cleanness in his sight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  \u201CWith the merciful you show yourself merciful;with the blameless
        man you show yourself blameless;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'with the purified you deal purely,and with the crooked you make yourself
        seem tortuous.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '  You save a humble people,  but your eyes are on the haughty to
        bring them down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  For you are my lamp, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and my God lightens
        my darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'For by you I can run against a troop,and by my God I can leap over
        a wall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "This God\u2014his way is perfect;the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        proves true;he is a shield for all those who take refuge in him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CFor who is God, but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?  And who
        is a rock, except our God?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'This God is my strong refugeand has made my[[COMMENT(0)]] way blameless.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:33 '
        content: 'Or ; also verse 34Compare Psalm 18:32; Hebrew , or '
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '  He made my feet like the feet of a deerand set me secure on the
        heights.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '  He trains my hands for war,so that my arms can bend a bow of bronze.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'You have given me the shield of your salvation,and your gentleness
        made me great.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: '  You gave a wide place for my steps under me,and my feet[[COMMENT(0)]]
        did not slip;  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:37 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'I pursued my enemies and destroyed them,and did not turn back until
        they were consumed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'I consumed them; I thrust them through, so that they did not rise;they
        fell under my feet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'For you equipped me with strength for the battle;you made those who
        rise against me sink under me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'You made my enemies turn their backs to me,[[COMMENT(0)]]those who
        hated me, and I destroyed them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:41 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'They looked, but there was none to save;they cried to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        but he did not answer them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'I beat them fine as the dust of the earth;I crushed them and stamped
        them down like the mire of the streets.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201CYou delivered me from strife with my people;[[COMMENT(0)]]you
        kept me as the head of the nations;  people whom I had not known served me.  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:44 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Foreigners came cringing to me;as soon as they heard of me, they
        obeyed me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Foreigners lost heartand came trembling[[COMMENT(0)]]  out of their
        fortresses.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:46 '
        content: 'Compare Psalm 18:45; Hebrew '
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, and blessed be my rock,and
        exalted be my God, the rock of my salvation,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'the God who gave me vengeanceand brought down peoples under me,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'who brought me out from my enemies;you exalted me above those who
        rose against me;you delivered me from men of violence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "  \u201CFor this I will praise you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        among the nations,and sing praises to your name.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "  Great salvation he brings[[COMMENT(0)]] to his king,and shows steadfast
        love to his anointed,to David and his offspring forever.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '22:51 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Last Words of David'
      title: The Last Words of David
      number: 1
      content: '  Now these are the last words of David:The oracle of David, the
        son of Jesse,the oracle of the man who was raised on high,  the anointed
        of the God of Jacob,the sweet psalmist of Israel:[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:1 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  \u201CThe Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> speaks by me;his
        word is on my tongue.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The God of Israel has spoken;  the Rock of Israel has said to me:When
        one rules justly over men,ruling in the fear of God,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'he dawns on them like the morning light,like the sun shining forth
        on a cloudless morning,like rain[[COMMENT(0)]] that makes grass to sprout
        from the earth.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:4 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CFor does not my house stand so with God?  For he has made with
        me an everlasting covenant,ordered in all things and secure.For will he not
        cause to prosperall my help and my desire?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But worthless men[[COMMENT(0)]] are all like thorns that are thrown
        away,for they cannot be taken with the hand;  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: "7: David\u2019s Mighty Men"
      title: "David\u2019s Mighty Men"
      number: 7
      content: "but the man who touches themarms himself with iron and the shaft
        of a spear,and they are utterly consumed with fire.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:7 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  These are the names of the mighty men whom David had: Josheb-basshebeth
        a Tahchemonite; he was chief of the three.[[COMMENT(0)]] He wielded his spear
        against eight hundred whom he killed at one time.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:8 '
        content: Or Compare 1 Chronicles 11:11; the meaning of the Hebrew expression
          is uncertain
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And next to him among the three mighty men was Eleazar the son of
        Dodo, son of Ahohi. He was with David when they defied the Philistines who
        were gathered there for battle, and the men of Israel withdrew. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He rose and struck down the Philistines until his hand was weary,
        and his hand clung to the sword. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> brought
        about a great victory that day, and the men returned after him only to strip
        the slain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And next to him was Shammah, the son of Agee the Hararite. The Philistines
        gathered together at Lehi,[[COMMENT(0)]] where there was a plot of ground
        full of lentils, and the men fled from the Philistines. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But he took his stand in the midst of the plot and defended it and
        struck down the Philistines, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> worked a
        great victory.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And three of the thirty chief men went down and came about harvest
        time to David at the cave of Adullam, when a band of Philistines was encamped
        in the Valley of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'David was then in the stronghold, and the garrison of the Philistines
        was then at Bethlehem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And David said longingly, \u201COh, that someone would give me water
        to drink from the well of Bethlehem that is by the gate!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the three mighty men broke through the camp of the Philistines
        and drew water out of the well of Bethlehem that was by the gate and carried
        and brought it to David. But he would not drink of it. He poured it out to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "and said, \u201CFar be it from me, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        that I should do this. Shall I drink the blood of the men who went at the
        risk of their lives?\u201D Therefore he would not drink it. These things
        the three mighty men did.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now Abishai, the brother of Joab, the son of Zeruiah, was chief of
        the thirty.[[COMMENT(0)]] And he wielded his spear against three hundred
        men and killed them and won a name beside the three. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:18 '
        content: 'Two Hebrew manuscripts, Syriac; most Hebrew manuscripts Or '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He was the most renowned of the thirty[[COMMENT(0)]] and became their
        commander, but he did not attain to the three.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:19 '
        content: 'Compare 1 Chronicles 11:21; Hebrew '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was a valiant man[[COMMENT(0)]] of
        Kabzeel, a doer of great deeds. He struck down two ariels of Moab. He also
        went down and struck down a lion in a pit on a day when snow had fallen. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:20 '
        content: Or The meaning of the word is unknown
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And he struck down an Egyptian, a handsome man. The Egyptian had
        a spear in his hand, but Benaiah went down to him with a staff and snatched
        the spear out of the Egyptian\u2019s hand and killed him with his own spear. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'These things did Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and won a name beside
        the three mighty men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He was renowned among the thirty, but he did not attain to the three.
        And David set him over his bodyguard.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  Asahel the brother of Joab was one of the thirty; Elhanan the son
        of Dodo of Bethlehem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Shammah of Harod, Elika of Harod, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Helez the Paltite, Ira the son of Ikkesh of Tekoa, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Abiezer of Anathoth, Mebunnai the Hushathite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Zalmon the Ahohite, Maharai of Netophah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Heleb the son of Baanah of Netophah, Ittai the son of Ribai of Gibeah
        of the people of Benjamin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Benaiah of Pirathon, Hiddai of the brooks of Gaash, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Abi-albon the Arbathite, Azmaveth of Bahurim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Eliahba the Shaalbonite, the sons of Jashen, Jonathan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Shammah the Hararite, Ahiam the son of Sharar the Hararite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Eliphelet the son of Ahasbai of Maacah, Eliam the son of Ahithophel
        the Gilonite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Hezro[[COMMENT(0)]]  of Carmel, Paarai the Arbite, '
      comments:
      - number: '23:35 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Igal the son of Nathan of Zobah, Bani the Gadite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai of Beeroth, the armor-bearer of Joab
        the son of Zeruiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Ira the Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Uriah the Hittite: thirty-seven in all.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Census"
      title: "David\u2019s Census"
      number: 1
      content: "      Again the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was kindled
        against Israel, and he incited David against them, saying, \u201CGo, number
        Israel and Judah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So the king said to Joab, the commander of the army,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        who was with him, \u201CGo through all the tribes of Israel, from Dan to
        Beersheba, and number the people, that I may know the number of the people.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '24:2 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Joab said to the king, \u201CMay the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God add to the people a hundred times as many as they are, while the
        eyes of my lord the king still see it, but why does my lord the king delight
        in this thing?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the king\u2019s word prevailed against Joab and the commanders
        of the army. So Joab and the commanders of the army went out from the presence
        of the king to number the people of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They crossed the Jordan and began from Aroer,[[COMMENT(0)]] and from
        the city that is in the middle of the valley, toward Gad and on to Jazer. '
      comments:
      - number: '24:5 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then they came to Gilead, and to Kadesh in the land of the Hittites;[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and they came to Dan, and from Dan they went around to Sidon, '
      comments:
      - number: '24:6 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and came to the fortress of Tyre and to all the cities of the Hivites
        and Canaanites; and they went out to the Negeb of Judah at Beersheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So when they had gone through all the land, they came to Jerusalem
        at the end of nine months and twenty days. '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: The \u2019s Judgment of David\u2019s Sin"
      title: "The \u2019s Judgment of David\u2019s Sin"
      number: 9
      content: 'And Joab gave the sum of the numbering of the people to the king:
        in Israel there were 800,000 valiant men who drew the sword, and the men
        of Judah were 500,000.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But David\u2019s heart struck him after he had numbered the people.
        And David said to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CI have sinned greatly
        in what I have done. But now, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, please take
        away the iniquity of your servant, for I have done very foolishly.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And when David arose in the morning, the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        came to the prophet Gad, David\u2019s seer, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CGo and say to David, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        Three things I offer[[COMMENT(0)]] you. Choose one of them, that I may do
        it to you.\u2019\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '24:12 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So Gad came to David and told him, and said to him, \u201CShall three[[COMMENT(0)]]
        years of famine come to you in your land? Or will you flee three months before
        your foes while they pursue you? Or shall there be three days\u2019 pestilence
        in your land? Now consider, and decide what answer I shall return to him
        who sent me.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '24:13 '
        content: 'Compare 1 Chronicles 21:12, Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then David said to Gad, \u201CI am in great distress. Let us fall
        into the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for his mercy is great;
        but let me not fall into the hand of man.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent a pestilence on Israel
        from the morning until the appointed time. And there died of the people from
        Dan to Beersheba 70,000 men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And when the angel stretched out his hand toward Jerusalem to destroy
        it, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> relented from the calamity and said to
        the angel who was working destruction among the people, \u201CIt is enough;
        now stay your hand.\u201D And the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was by the threshing floor of Araunah the Jebusite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: David Builds an Altar'
      title: David Builds an Altar
      number: 17
      content: "Then David spoke to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> when he saw the
        angel who was striking the people, and said, \u201CBehold, I have sinned,
        and I have done wickedly. But these sheep, what have they done? Please let
        your hand be against me and against my father\u2019s house.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Gad came that day to David and said to him, \u201CGo up, raise
        an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> on the threshing floor of Araunah
        the Jebusite.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So David went up at Gad\u2019s word, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        commanded. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And when Araunah looked down, he saw the king and his servants coming
        on toward him. And Araunah went out and paid homage to the king with his
        face to the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Araunah said, \u201CWhy has my lord the king come to his servant?\u201D
        David said, \u201CTo buy the threshing floor from you, in order to build
        an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, that the plague may be averted
        from the people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Araunah said to David, \u201CLet my lord the king take and offer
        up what seems good to him. Here are the oxen for the burnt offering and the
        threshing sledges and the yokes of the oxen for the wood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "All this, O king, Araunah gives to the king.\u201D And Araunah said
        to the king, \u201CMay the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God accept you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But the king said to Araunah, \u201CNo, but I will buy it from you
        for a price. I will not offer burnt offerings to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        my God that cost me nothing.\u201D So David bought the threshing floor and
        the oxen for fifty shekels[[COMMENT(0)]] of silver. "
      comments:
      - number: '24:24 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And David built there an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings. So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        responded to the plea for the land, and the plague was averted from Israel.
      comments: []
